# Workflow Rule

Canonical source: `AGENTS.md` sections `Working model` and `Task spec rule`.

Execution-critical reminders:
- Before editing, reread the active spec's `In Scope`, `Allowed Edits`, `Done When`, and validation path. Durable specs live only in `ai/doc/specs/`.
- Execute spec-bound work via `ai/skill/execute-from-spec.md`; a tiny task may skip spec creation only when it is already effectively spec-complete and trivially narrow.
- If repair or follow-up would exceed the active spec, stop for `replan_required` or `needs_decision` via `ai/skill/replan-or-escalate.md` instead of widening the task.
- When the repository uses `project/*` and the completed slice makes a project control layer stale, update `project/CURRENT.md`, `project/memory/*`, `project/DOC_MAP.md`, `project/decisions/*`, or `project/experiments/*` in the same change; use `ai/skill/session-closeout.md` to make that decision explicit.
